body: "## Charter\nLiving log of Architecture Decision Records. Each ADR is a Decision item under this epic capturing context, the decision, consequences, and evidence for an architectural choice actually made (not aspirational). 38 closed ADRs at 2026-07-04 (e.g. pm-w13j literal all-src coverage gate).\n\n## Conventions\n- ADR titles: \"ADR: <date or topic> — <decision>\".\n- ADRs close when the decision is recorded and its consequences are reflected in code/docs; they are historical records, so closed ADRs are never edited retroactively (append comments instead).\n- One open child: pm-96wm (2026-06-07 deep-audit ADR) stays open as its remediation batches are still being verified; close it once every deferred finding it indexes is filed or shipped."
